$ SQL Server - sys.syslogins
@ sys.syslogins

`sys.syslogins` shows *login accounts*.

Microsoft recommends to use → development/databases/SQL-Server/administration/schemas/sys/objects/views/sql_logins[`sys.sql_logins`] and
→ development/databases/SQL-Server/administration/schemas/sys/objects/views/server_principals[`sys.server_principals`] instead of `sys.syslogins`.


sa:
  → development/databases/SQL-Server/administration/schemas/sys/objects/stored-procedures/sp_helplogins[`sp_helplogins`]

  → development/databases/SQL-Server/administration/schemas/sys/objects/views/sysusers[`sys.sysusers`]

  The → development/databases/SQL-Server/administration/schemas/sys[sys schema]
